89
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:04,120
What?

90
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:23,670
<i>[Legend of One-inch Princess]</i>

91
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:30,860
Takagi-kun.

92
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:33,040
Sensei.

93
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:41,550
Oh, so you have known that Moon Bunny Michaela was Horikiri-san.

94
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,940
Yes.

95
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:47,070
She must have based "Chobiko in a Pocket" on this.

96
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:50,830
The setting of the stories are similar.

97
00:07:50,890 --> 00:07:55,480
I wonder why Horikiri-san started writing a new story though.

98
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:58,590
"Blue Fairy" was getting into a really interesting part of the story.

99
00:07:58,590 --> 00:08:07,950
Perhaps, something happened to her state of mind, I think.

100
00:08:07,950 --> 00:08:10,660
Something happened to her state of mind...?

101
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:15,020
<i>When I wrote what's been collecting inside me, it happend...</i>

102
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:22,630
<i>I guess that is a mental scenary that is inside your heart.</i>

103
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:26,840
"Chobiko in a Pocket"...

104
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:30,710
That must be the mental scenary in her mind right now.

105
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:33,830
Could it be that she became Chobiko?

106
00:08:33,830 --> 00:08:35,150
Eh?

107
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:37,340
I'm kidding.

108
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:40,830
Oh, but it could be...

109
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:42,660
What?

110
00:08:42,660 --> 00:08:47,060
Horikiri-shi might be having impossible love.

111
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,550
What makes you say so?

112
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:52,910
Chobiko loves the big guy who she can't possibly be together with.

113
00:08:52,910 --> 00:09:01,370
The gap in the height of them might represent the alienation she feels for him from not being able to be with him.

114
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:04,370
I see...

115
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:08,800
